body:
I think this is a good start indeed, thank you @mvdan 

```
func VeryLong(param1 T1, param2 T2, [...],
    param6 T6, param7 T7,
) {
    doWork(...)
}
```

The only thing that we want to avoid is to make it even less readable, imagine we have a soft limit to 120 characters per line

```
func (mylongstructure *MyLongNameOfCompilcatedTypeThatYouShouldNeverDo) DoTheVeryLongNameAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA(p T0, 
    param1 T1, param2 T3,
) {
    doWork(...)
}

```

Now you can see that `p T0` is on the first line and it's really easy to miss it.


What if gofumpt will force parameters on long lines always go on the next line?
```
func VeryLongAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA
    p T0, param1 T1, param2 T3,
) {
    doWork(...)
}
```
